An Italian, French and Indian went for a job interview in England.<br>Before the interview, they were told that they must compose a sentence in<br>English with three main words: green, pink and yellow..<br><br>The Italian was first: "I wake up in the morning. I see the yellow<br>sun. I see the green grass and I think to myself, I hope it will be a pink day.."<br><br>The French was next: " I wake up in the morning, I eat a yellow banana,<br>a green pepper and in the evening I watch the pink panter on TV..<br><br>Last was the Indian, : "I wake up in the morning, I hear the phone<br><br>"green green", I "pink" up the phone and I say "Yellow"